docs.snippet: The dollar was irregularly lower last week, measured by the quotation for the French franc. Monday witnessed the best premium of the week when there was established a .9 cent advantage, but pressure against the dollar sent it down to close at .5 cent...
docs.lead_paragraph: The dollar was irregularly lower last week, measured by the quotation for the French franc. Monday witnessed the best premium of the week when there was established a .9 cent advantage, but pressure against the dollar sent it down to close at .5 cent premium, a slight loss over the preceding week. The range a year ago was 99.69@99.53 cent.
